ter to join the HMBT.  For more than 20 years now she has been a strong pillar to the order.  Today she spends most of her time running the day to day affairs of the Sahar Orphanage.  She also teaches at a nearby private school,  and through this employment,  brings in financial support to run the orphanage.</p>\r\n&nbsp;','Sr. Eliza','','publish','open','open','','eliza','','','2014-03-13 02:38:32','2014-03-13 02:38:32','',7,'http://handmaids-local/?page_id=23',1,'page','',0),(24,1,'2014-01-18 03:37:56','2014-01-18 03:37:56','This is a story about Eliza.','Eliza','','inherit','open','open','','23-revision-v1','','','2014-01-18 03:37:56','2014-01-18 03:37:56','',23,'http://handmaids-local/uncategorized/23-revision-v1',0,'revision','',0),(25,1,'2014-01-18 03:38:36','2014-01-18 03:38:36','<p dir=\"ltr\"><a href=\"http://www.vitalypeker.com/handmaids/wordpress/wp-content/uploads/DSC01043-Small.jpg\"><img class=\"aligncenter size-full wp-image-257\" alt=\"DSC01043 (Small)\" src=\"http://www.vitalypeker.com/handmaids/wordpress/wp-content/uploads/DSC01043-Small.jpg\" width=\"640\" height=\"480\" /></a></p>\r\n<p dir=\"ltr\">Sr. Paulette comes from a Christian Indian family from the island of Mauritus.  In her youth she decided to become a nun and came to Calcutta to join Mother Teresa.  For about 20 years she worked with Mother Teresa mainly helping women and children and doing family planning work.  She developed a severe back condition which required hospitalization. She was sent to a Mumbai hospital where she spent several months.  When she emerged from recuperation Mother Teresa urged her to remain in Mumbai in a life of service.  This is how, in 1989,  she became the foundress of a new order of nuns called the Handmaids of the Blessed Trinity.  Today the order contains about 40 nuns;  about 10 of these are directly working with Sr. Paulette at the orphanages.</p>\r\n&nbsp;','Sr. Paulette','','publish','open','open','','paulette','','','2014-03-15 19:01:32','2014-03-1