arriage she was brought to the Merces Orphanage about a year ago.\r\n\r\nRuby\'s favorite subjects in school are Speech (in which she enters competitions) and Singing (for which she has won awards).  She hopes someday to be a doctor because it is \"a respectable career\".   She really values all the people caring for her at the orphanage and feels a sense of community.  She said she would rather stay at the orphanage than to go back to her previous life.','Ruby Kureshi','','publish','open','open','','ruby-kureshi','','','2014-03-12 13:43:12','2014-03-12 13:43:12','',151,'http://handmaids-local/?page_id=156',2,'page','',0),(157,1,'2014-02-26 04:44:05','2014-02-26 04:44:05','','Ruby Kureshi','','inherit','open','open','','156-revision-v1','','','2014-02-26 04:44:05','2014-02-26 04:44:05','',156,'http://handmaids-local/uncategorized/156-revision-v1',0,'revision','',0),(158,1,'2014-02-26 04:44:41','2014-02-26 04:44:41','<a href=\"http://www.vitalypeker.com/handmaids/wordpress/wp-content/uploads/DSC01040-Small.jpg\"><img class=\"aligncenter size-full wp-image-255\" alt=\"DSC01040 (Small)\" src=\"http://www.vitalypeker.com/handmaids/wordpress/wp-content/uploads/DSC01040-Small.jpg\" width=\"480\" height=\"640\" /></a>Supriya is currently in 6th standard and has lived at the Merces Orphanage since 2007.   When both her parents died of tuberculosis she was brought to the orphanage by her grandmother who  had to go to work and had no means to support her.   She is expected to return to her grandmother after 10th grade but she is not sure she wants to go back.   She has one brother who is 14 years old who lives in another orphanage and visits on Sundays.\r\n\r\nSupriya attends St. Anthony\'s Convent School where she is average in her class of 80 kids.  She hopes to be an aritist someday.','Supriya Naka','','publish','open','open','','supriya-naka','','','2014-03-12 13:45:13','2014-03-12 13:45:13','',151,'http://handmaids-local/?page_id=158',4,'page','',0),(159,1,'2014-02-26 04:44:41','2014-02-26 04:44:41','','Supriya Naka','','inherit','open','open','','158-revision-v1','','','2014-02-26 04:44:41','2014-02-26 04:44:41','',158,'http://handmaids-local/uncategorized/158-revision-v1',0,'revision','',0),(160,1,'2014-02-26 04:45:14','2014-02-26 04:45:14','<a href=\"http://www.vitalypeker.com/handmaids/wordpress/wp-content/uploads/DSC01041-Small.jpg\"><img class=\"aligncenter size-full wp-image-256\" alt=\"DSC01041 (Small)\" src=\"http://www.vitalypeker.com/handmaids/wordpress/wp-content/uploads/DSC01041-Small.jpg\" width=\"640\" height=\"480\" /></a>Arti was born in September 1998.  Her father divorced her mother and ran away.  Her mother works as a live-in-maid in someone\'s house and is unable to have Arti with her but visits her on Sundays.\r\n\r\nShe is currently in the 8th standard and has lived at Merces Orphanage since 2009.  She hopes someday to become a police officer because she \"wants to enforce justice\".','Arti Gaikwade','','publish','open','open','','arti-gaikwade','','','2014-03-12 13:45:39','2014-03-12 13:45:39','',151,'http://handmaids-local/?page_id=160',5,'page','',0),(161,1,'2014-02-26 04:45:14','2014-02-26 04:45:14','','Arti Gaikwade','','inherit','open','open','','160-revision-v1','','','2014-02-26 04:45:14','2014-02-26 04:45:14','',160,'http://handmaids-local/uncategorized/160-revision-v1',0,'revision','',0),(162,1,'2014-02-26 04:46:30','2014-02-26 04:46:30','<p style=\"text-align: justify;\"><span style=\"line-height: 1.5em;\"><a href=\"http://www.vitalypeker.com/handmaids/wordpress/wp-content/uploads/DSC01134-Custom.jpg\"><img class=\"size-full wp-image-374 alignleft\" alt=\"DSC01134 (Custom)\" src=\"http://www.vitalypeker.com/handmaids/wordpress/wp-content/uploads/DSC01134-Custom.jpg\" width=\"240\" height=\"320\" /></a>\r\n</span></p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\"><a href=\"http://www.vitalypeker.com/handmaids/wordpress/wp-content/uploads/DSC01136-Custom.jpg\"><img class=\"aligncenter size-full wp-image-375\" alt=\"DSC01136 (Custom)\" src=\"http://www.vitalypeker.com/handmaids/wordpress/wp-content/uploads/DSC01136-Custom.jpg\" width=\"320\" height=\"240\" /></a></p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">                                                                                                                                                                     Gauri</p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">                          Tulsi</p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">Tulsi was born November 2003 and her sister Gauri was born April 2005.  Both are living at the Sahar Orphanage.  They are in 3rd and 2nd standard respectively.  Their mother died in a road accident.  Their father had no job and was homeless so he brought the girls to the orphanage.   He hopes to collect them after they complete school through the 7th standard at Sahar,  by which time he hopes his personal situation will have improved.</p>','Tulsi & Gauri Shetty','','publish','open','open','','tulsi-gauri-shetty','','','2014-03-13 13:18:28','2014-03-13 13:18:28','',151,'http://handmaids-local/?page_id=162',3,'page','',0),(163,1,'2014-02-26 04:46:30','2014-02-26 04:46:30','','Tulsi & Gauri Shetty','','inherit','open','open','','162-revision-v1','','','2014-02-26 04:46:30','2014-02-26 04:46:30','',162,'http://handmaids-local/uncategorized/162-revision-v1',0,'revision','',0),(164,1,'2014-02-26 04:47:01','2014-02-26 04:47:01','<p style=\"text-align: left;\"><a href=\"http://www.vitalypeker.com/handmaids/wordpress/wp-content/uploads/DSC01140-Small.jpg\"><img class=\"aligncenter  wp-image-294\" alt=\"DSC01140 (Small)\" src=\"http://www.vitalypeker.com/handmaids/wordpress/wp-content/uploads/DSC01140-Small.jpg\" width=\"384\" height=\"288\" /></a></p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: left;\">Sneha was born September 2003.   She is currently healthy.  She has been living at the Sahar Orphanage since the age of 3 when she was brought there by her grandmother who still visits.</p>\r\nHer father had burned her mother to death over a property dispute and spent some time in jail.  His brother bought for him his way out of jail within the corrupt system in India.  He is forbidden from seeing Sneha.  Her brother Sopnil is 2 years older.  He was living at the Merces Orphange but is currently at another orphanage.\r\n\r\nShe attends 3rd standard at the Sahar Orphanage School and is maintaining an average academic performance in her class of 50 students.','Sneha Borde','','publish','open','open','','sneha-borde','','','2014-03-15 19:20:46','2014-03-15 19:20:46','',151,'http://handmaids-local/?page_id=164',0,'page','',0),(165,1,'2014-02-26 04:47:01','2014-02-26 04:47:01','','Sneha Borde','','inherit','open','open','','164-revision-v1','','','2014-02-26 04:47:01','2014-02-26 04:47:01','',164,'http://handmaids-local/uncategorized/164-revision-v1',0,'revision','',0),(166,1,'2014-03-13 03:19:30','2014-03-13 03:19:30','The left side bar of this page will take you to a few, typical profiles of the orphans.\n\nThere are about 30 orphans at Sahar and about 100 at Merces-Giriz.  They range from 3 years to 16 years old.  Their parents have died either due to disease, violent crime,  self neglect,  or are in prison.\n\nSome of the kids are not \"orphans\" but have been brought by a parent or family member because they are physically or financially unable to care for them.  Often, there will be one surviving parent or a distant relative that continues to visit their child at the orphanages and this individual will eventually accept the child back.   But while they are there, the HMBT Sisters care for them completely.\n\nOn a typical day they will arise at 5:30-6:00 am.  After eating breakfast they will get dressed and ready for school which  goes till the early afternoon.   At Sahar the school is within the orphanage house itself;  at Merces-Giriz the kids take a bus or walk to nearby independent schools.   In the mid-afternoon there is additonal tutoring by a paid teacher at Sahar and by volunteer local college students at Merces-Giriz.  In the late afternoon the kids all do homework,  chores, have play time,  take baths, eat dinner and have prayer time.  They typically go to bed around 9 pm.    On Sundays, there is extra time for watching T.V.,  having a party, music, dance,  and also visits by family members or persons from the community.\n\n&nbsp;','Orphan Profiles','','inherit','open','open','','151-autosave-v1','','','2014-03-13 03:19:30','2014-03-13 03:19:30','',151,'http://handmaids-local/uncategorized/151-autosave-v1',0,'revision','',0),(167,1,'2014-02-26 04:55:11','2014-02-26 04:55:11','There are about 30 orphans at Sahar and about 100 at Merces-Giriz.  They range from 3 years to 16 years old.  Their parents have died either due to disease or violent crime or self neglect or are in prison.  Often, there will be one surviving parent or a distant relative that continues to visit their child at the orphanages and will eventually accept them back.   On this page you will find the profiles of some typical orphans.','Orphans','','inherit','open','open','','151-revision-v1','','','2014-02-26 04:55:11','2014-02-26 04:55:11','',151,'http://handmaids-local/uncategorized/151-revision-v1',0,'revision','',0),(168,1,'2014-02-26 04:58:15','2014-02-26 04:58:15','This is the projects page','Current Needs','','inherit','open','open','','34-revision-v1','','','2014-02-26 04:58:15','2014-02-26 04:58:15','',34,'http://handmaids-local/uncategorized/34-revision-v1',0,'revision','',0),(169,1,'2014-02-26 05:00:40','2014-02-26 05:00:40','*  The main orphanage house at Merces has a leaking roof over the room in which  the kids have shelves to put their school bags and books.  The sisters would like to remedy this by constructing a covered terrace above this room which will also give a space to hang up all the laundry to dry.  Currently the clothes are washed by hand as part of the chores of the orphans.   There is no covered place to hang laundry for drying - so there i