h 7th standard and has 300 kids, all packed tightly in the orphanage house which is about 2000 square feet.  A typical classroom is about 200 square feet and holds about 30 kids.  The teachers, who come from nearby communities,  are paid 400 Rupees per month.  The children attending this school have no other viable option.  They are unable to go to the already impacted government schools and nearby private schools are unaffordable.  The HMBT school offers a low cost English medium education in subjects ranging from science, to math, to crafts, to language.  Were it not for this school, many of the kids would receive no education.  At Merces - Giriz the orphans all attend local independent schools, the cost of which is borne by the HMBT','History','','inherit','open','open','','141-revision-v1','','','2014-02-26 14:23:17','2014-02-26 14:23:17','',141,'http://handmaids-local/uncategorized/141-revision-v1',0,'revision','',0),(196,1,'2014-02-26 14:27:29','2014-02-26 14:27:29','Ruby was born in June 1999.   Both of her parents passed away of unknown causes.  She was living with her sister but upon her sister\'s marriage she was brought to the Merces Orphanage about a year ago.\n\nRuby\'s favorite subjects in school are Speech (in which she enters competitions) and Singing (for which she has won awards).  She hopes someday to be a doctor because it is \"a respectable career\".   She really values all the people caring for her at the orphanage and feels a sense of community.  She said sh','Ruby Kureshi','','inherit','open','open','','156-autosave-v1','','','2014-02-26 14:27:29','2014-02-26 14:27:29','',156,'http://handmaids-local/uncategorized/156-autosave-v1',0,'revision','',0),(197,1,'2014-02-26 14:27:55','2014-02-26 14:27:55','Ruby was born in June 1999.   Both of her parents passed away of unknown causes.  She was living with her sister but upon her sister\'s marriage she was brought to the Merces Orphanage about a year ago.\r\n\r\nRuby\'s favorite subjects in school a