jpg\" width=\"640\" height=\"480\" /></a>Sneha was born September 2003.   She is currently healthy.  She has been living at the Sahar Orphanage since the age of 3 when she was brought there by her grandmother who still visits.\r\n\r\nHer father had burned her mother to death over a property dispute and spent some time in jail.  His brother bought for him his way out of jail within the corrupt system in India.  He is forbidden from seeing Sneha.  Her brother Sopnil is 2 years older.  He was living at the Merces Orphange but is currently at another orphanage.\r\n\r\nShe attends 3rd standard at the Sahar Orphanage School and is maintaining an average academic performance in her class of 50 students.','Sneha Borde','','inherit','open','open','','164-revision-v1','','','2014-03-12 13:17:50','2014-03-12 13:17:50','',164,'http://handmaids-local/uncategorized/164-revision-v1',0,'revision','',0),(349,1,'2014-03-12 13:19:41','2014-03-12 13:19:41','<a href=\"http://www.vitalypeker.com/handmaids/wordpress/wp-content/uploads/DSC01035-Small.jpg\"><img class=\"aligncenter size-full wp-image-253\" alt=\"DSC01035 (Small)\" src=\"http://www.vitalypeker.com/handmaids/wordpress/wp-content/uploads/DSC01035-Small.jpg\" width=\"640\" height=\"480\" /></a>Preeti was born in April 2000.  She has been living at Merces Orphanage since the age of 5.   Her dad died of tuberculosis just before.   Her mother brought her to the orphange because she couldn\'t take care of her.  In 2013 her mother also died of tuberculosis.   Preeti has been treated and cured.\r\n\r\nPreeti is first in her class of 47 students at nearby St. Thomas High School where she takes Geography,  English,  History, Science, Math, Drawing and a computer class.  Her favorite subject is English.  She hopes to become a teacher someday.  She is very happy to be living at this orphanage and is greatful to the sisters for looking after her.','Preeti Kutade','','inherit','open','open','','154-revision-v1','','','2014-03-12 13:19:41',