sistance to do much needed building construction.  Previously they were literally residing in huts or make shift domiciles without a roof.\r\n\r\n<a href=\"http://www.vitalypeker.com/handmaids/wordpress/wp-content/uploads/DSCF6974-Mobile.jpg\"><img class=\"alignnone size-full wp-image-459\" alt=\"DSCF6974 (Mobile)\" src=\"http://www.vitalypeker.com/handmaids/wordpress/wp-content/uploads/DSCF6974-Mobile.jpg\" width=\"427\" height=\"320\" /></a>\r\n\r\nOver the years,  their organization and their reach has grown.  The sisters have had to overcome many challenges in being responsible for all the orphans under their care.\r\n\r\n<a href=\"http://www.vitalypeker.com/handmaids/wordpress/wp-content/uploads/DSCF7190-Mobile.jpg\"><img class=\"alignnone size-full wp-image-457\" alt=\"DSCF7190 (Mobile)\" src=\"http://www.vitalypeker.com/handmaids/wordpress/wp-content/uploads/DSCF7190-Mobile.jpg\" width=\"427\" height=\"320\" /></a>\r\n\r\n<a href=\"http://www.vitalypeker.com/handmaids/wordpress/wp-content/uploads/DSCF7475-Mobile.jpg\"><img class=\"alignnone size-full wp-image-464\" alt=\"DSCF7475 (Mobile)\" src=\"http://www.vitalypeker.com/handmaids/wordpress/wp-content/uploads/DSCF7475-Mobile.jpg\" width=\"427\" height=\"320\" /></a>\r\n\r\nThen, and even now, the sisters often arise at 5 in the morning and don’t retire till late at night attending to their missionary work diligently.  They have grown as an order from just 2 nuns to recently about 40 nuns.  About 10 of these are involved with the orphanages in Mumbai and the remainder are doing parish work in other parts of India.\r\n\r\nThe orphanages  have evolved gradually into becoming girls only orphanages today.  The boys  previously living there have all been placed with other orphanages or extended family.  For practical reasons it was not possible to have co-ed orphanages.  The boys were often disruptive around girls, not having any male residential mentors or father figures.  Also,  it was not possible to maintain 